article.headline: Southern Methodist 68, Centenary 40
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Derrick Roberts scored 19 points and Ike Ofoegbu grabbed 11 rebounds to lead SMU to a 68-40 win over Centenary on Saturday. Roberts was 6-of-7 from the field and 5-of-6 from the 3-point range. He also pulled in four rebounds. SMU (8-1) had four players in double figures as Brian Epps scored 14 points, Ofoegbu 13 and Bamba Fall 12. SMU extended its winning streak to six games. Centenary (4-6) was led by Tyrone Hamilton who scored 16 points on 5-of-19 shooting from the floor. He missed all of his eight 3-point attempts. SMU (8-1) took an early 11-2 lead on consecutive 3-pointers and held a 43-19 halftime lead. The Mustangs outrebounded Centenary 45-17 and shot 54 percent for the game from the field. The Gents shot 30 percent from the field.
